Hi there,

=C2=A0
It's Emma from Hayden Flour Mills. I just published a [new video on YouTube=
](https://www.youtube.com/@Haydenflourmills). It's about something I've bee=
n thinking about and I'm inviting our community to help shape what comes ne=
xt.

[ WATCH THE VIDEO ](https://www.youtube.com/@Haydenflourmills)

https://youtu.be/iAsfhxWd8GQ?si=3D_2CcYEPmW0EpzazL

As the co-owner of Hayden Flour Mills, I think about soil, water, and carin=
g for the land. My dad and I grow and mill heritage grains with intention. =
But one part of our process didn=E2=80=99t sit right with me: the plastic b=
ag.=C2=A0
=C2=A0
Plastic is everywhere because it=E2=80=99s cheap and easy, but it doesn=E2=
=80=99t disappear. It fragments, travels, and accumulates, often ending up =
in landfills, oceans, and even our food. I couldn=E2=80=99t stop thinking a=
bout that gap.

[ WATCH THE VIDEO ](https://www.youtube.com/@Haydenflourmills)

https://www.youtube.com/@Haydenflourmills

RETHINKING THE BAG

In my own home, I try to run a low-waste household. I compost and garden. W=
atching food scraps and compostable materials turn back into soil, I realiz=
ed I wanted that same care to extend to how our flour reaches you. So I've =
been working on something: a trial run of fully compostable flour bags.

https://haydenflourmills.com/products/white-sonora-all-purpose-flour

NEW! COMPOSTABLE BAGS=C2=A0

These bags are designed to break down fully within months=E2=80=94in your c=
ompost bin, your backyard garden, or a local composting program. Instead of=
 lingering for centuries, they return to enrich the earth. It's another way=
 to leave more goodness in the world than we take out.

https://haydenflourmills.com/products/white-sonora-all-purpose-flour

VOTE FOR WHAT COMES NEXT
=C2=A0
